<p><span></span></p>
<h2><span>Interpretation of the lion in a dream for Fahd al-Asimi</span></h2>
<p>Seeing <strong>a lion in a dream</strong> like other symbols can have multiple meanings, depending on the time and circumstances of the viewer.  The most important of what is said about it is as follows:</p>
<p>Lions in a dream may be among the meanings of seeing him in staying away from the remembrance, leaving the work of the teachings of religion, and contemplating the saying of the Almighty: As if they were red glowing coals fleeing from the enclosures, and the enclosure is a lion as Abu Hurayrah and others interpreted it.<br/>And <a href="https://gptafser.com/post/تفسير-رؤية-الأسود-في-المنام?page=3847" > seeing lions </a> may indicate the danger of the road, especially for those who travel, and may mean that there are bad deals from customs, for example, or at the border from which the traveler will leave, and this is because the lion in nature plays roles similar to these roles.<br/>Seeing <a href="https://gptafser.com/post/رؤية-الأسد-في-المنام-لابن-سيرين?page=578" > a lion </a> in a dream means that the dreamer may face a serious and fatal disease or fever, and it is known that lions do not leave them suffering from fever, and this is scientifically proven, but also because the origin of evil is from the word lion and its plural is lions.</p><div class="angwp_84394 _ning_cont _ning_hidden _ning_outer _align_center responsive" data-aid="0" data-bid="84394" data-size="custom" style="max-width:100%; width:100%;height:inherit;"><div class="_ning_label _left" style=""></div><div class="_ning_inner" style=""><script type="text/javascript">
