</script></div></div><div class="clear"></div>
<p><span></span></p>
<p>The lion in a dream can refer to a harmful and corrupt animal, especially if it is seen by owners of farms or farmers.  And it has been proven by the authenticity of Abu Hurayrah that the lion is the poisonous dog.  Narrated by Imam Ibn Hazm – as in al-Muhala – page or number: 7/241, so in his view, there is a harmful or harmful animal to humans.<br/>This saying is supported by what the Prophet, peace be upon him, narrated that he was asked about the poisonous dog and said: He is the lion.</p>
<p>Among the meanings of seeing him is also the existence of indulgence in looking at the prohibited of the dreamer or whoever enters his house, and this has been proven in the hadith of Abu Hurayrah, may Allah be pleased with him:<br/>Beware of looking at the forbidden, so beware of the lion and it is narrated by a reliable authority, and this meaning is among the meanings that I find most applicable to <a href="https://gptafser.com/post/رؤية-الأسد-في-المنام-لابن-سيرين?page=578" > seeing a lion </a> at this time, especially for women.</p>
<p>Also, among the meanings of seeing him is the appearance of some wonderful verses or excellent worldly Sunnah, and contemplating what Abu Hurayrah, may Allah be pleased with him, narrated with a good chain of narrators on the authority of his master, peace be upon him, and prayers and peace be upon him, said:<br/>The son of Mary will descend as a righteous Imam and a just judge, so they will break the cross and kill the pig and restore peace and take swords as knives and destroy every block.  His food descends from the sky, and his blessing rises from the earth, until the child plays with the snake and it does not harm him, and he pastures the sheep and the wolf and it does not harm them, and he pastures the lion and the cows. and it does not harm them.<br/>Also look at what Abu Hurayrah, may Allah be pleased with him, narrated:<br/>Blessed is life after the Messiah, and blessed is life after the Messiah, and the sky is called for rain, and the earth is called to grow, so if you plant your seed in the earth, it will grow, and it will not be jealous or envious. or hated, until the man passes by the lion and it does not harm him, and he steps on the snake and it does not harm him, he does not argue, he does not envy, and he does not hate.<br/>Al-Albani – Source: Al-Silsila al-Sahiha – Page or number: 1926: Its chain of narration is sound.</p><div class="angwp_84394 _ning_cont _ning_hidden _ning_outer _align_center responsive" data-aid="0" data-bid="84394" data-size="custom" style="max-width:100%; width:100%;height:inherit;"><div class="_ning_label _left" style=""></div><div class="_ning_inner" style=""><script type="text/javascript">
